question.body:
After the following code runs, what will be the value of `result`?

```js
function f () { return g() + 10; }

var g = function () { return 10; }

var result = f();
```

After the following code runs, what will be the value of `result`?

```js
var result = f();

function f () { return g() + 10; }

var g = function () { return 10; }
```

After the following code runs, what will be the value of `result`?

```js
var result = f();

function f () { return 10; }

var g = function () { return 10; }
```

When running `foo()`, what will be the value of `result`?

```js
function foo () {
  var result = x;
  var x = 10;
}
```
